node.text:
🚨 WORLD RECORD 🚨

@yalemzerfyehualaw 🇪🇹 takes the win at @antrimcoasthalfmarathon and sets a world record for the women's half marathon in 1:03:44 (*the official time has been confirmed as 1:03:43.156, the world record time is therefore of 1:03:44 and not 1:03:43 as previously stated)!

She's the first woman to ever go sub-1:04 👏

#Athletics #WorldAthletics #WorldRecord #HalfMarathon

node.text:
"I think I could have done better but I'm happy," said @parchment_hansle 🇯🇲 after taking the win in the men's 110m hurdles at #ParisDL.

"I want to improve my technique by the end of the season. I'd like to go sub-13!"

📷 @matthewquine / @diamondleagueathletics

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by World Athletics on August 28, 2021 tagging @nicolalmcdermott. May be an image of 1 person and playing a sport.

node.text:
"I've been 2nd/3rd so many times this season, I'm glad to finally win," said @nicolalmcdermott 🇦🇺 after #ParisDL.

"I left my heart for the crowd today. I love to see full stadiums, and I love when people can enjoy athletics!"

Aw, Nicola... 💞

📷 @matthewquine / @diamondleagueathletics

node.text:
Making 10.72 look easy!

@fastelaine 🇯🇲 tears up the track at #ParisDL to take the win in the women’s 100m!

That’s the 𝘀𝗶𝘅𝘁𝗵 time she goes sub-10.8 this season!

📷 @matthewquine / @diamondleagueathletics
